⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
My baby is almost 8 months old and is starting to develop some food preferences. Lately there have been meals that I’ll share in stories where she eats just a small amount.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
A common question I’ve been receiving: Do I top her off with purées if she doesn’t eat enough at that meal?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Should we “top off” baby after meals? In short...NO.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
With baby led feeding (whether that’s purées or finger foods), we choose what foods to serve however we allow our little one to determine HOW MUCH of these they want to eat. We allow THEM to eat according to their hunger and fullness. Because after all, isn’t that the ultimate goal?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I know this can be difficult and is WAY more complex than I can fit into a single post. 🙏 This is why in the Starting Solids Program we have 6 weeks to work on it 🙌🏼 I’m going to walk you through how to SAFELY transition from purées to family meals🍽 while ensuring your babe IS eating enough with SELF-feeding.
