I know I’ve been there, and I’m a lactation consultant!! 
Once your milk supply regulates and You no longer feel engorged, it’s easy to think you don’t have milk, but this isn’t true.

✔️is baby gaining weight?
✔️is baby having adequate output?
✔️is baby overall content after feedings?
✔️do you hear swallows?

Then you’re making milk mama. Trust your body and trust your baby. 

Sure there are things that can decrease supply like stress, menstrual cycle, pregnancy, infrequent or inefficient milk removal, medications etc, but for the most part, if your breasts are being emptied and you just happen to “feel soft”, you’re still making milk 😉

Did you doubt your supply because you felt soft?
 

