.
.
I graduated in 2008 from @yorkuniversity with my Bachelor's of Science in Nursing degree and knew pretty early on I wanted to work on the health promotion side of nursing so in 2009 I started working in public health. 
.
.
I completed my Masters of Public Health in 2013 at @uofwaterloo.
.
.
 While working as a nurse I continued to see people's diet causing disease and wanted to learn more about food being used to heal and nourish which lead me to complete my Holistic Nutritionist training at @instituteofholisticnutrition. 
.
.
I've been working with moms and moms to be for the past 6 years and the benefits of breastfeeding were always a huge part of my health teaching. It wasnt until I had my own children that breastfeeding became such an interest and passion for me. Its the perfect food for human babies! And it makes me super sad and frustrated when moms dont get to breastfeed whether from lack of knowledge or support which has lead me to go back to school (AGAIN) to become a International Board Certified Lactation Consultant! 
.
.
I started my course this week and love it. I write my exam in April 2021! I'm super excited to continue to support women to acheive optimal health particularly during their breastfeeding journey! 
.
.
.
